reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great board, but no mounting bolts included
reviews.reviewText: Notched one star out of "Tech Support" for this M/B not shipping with a packet of bolts that secure board to a case. This should not be a problem if you do a M/B upgrade and retain those bolts after removing old M/B. Still, why would company that sells a M/B ships me a SATA cable for a drive that is not part of the deal, but fails to supply bolts for the M/B that it actually does sell? I had an all new build and had to scramble to find correct bolts.Otherwise board is good, no problems installing it and most drivers came straight from Win 11. I only had to run Intel INF installer on top of it.In fact this M/B was my second choice, but the first choice board from MSI had a problem getting GPU card initialized, going into a boot cycle half way into POST. I always considered MSI a good brand, but now I wonder how much of a QA they do these days. Installing M/B just to find that it is defective is quite a pain, considering CPU/fan/paste shenanigans involved. I say, spend extra $20 and get this board instead. Just make sure you have those bolts lined up for installation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good budget board
reviews.reviewText: Everything works as it should. Only thing annoying are the SATA ports on the board. For whatever reason, on this model they are upside-down compared to other boards I've used. Even other Gigabyte boards. So you have to bend the SATA cable on top of itself when using the "L" connector. Makes for a less clean install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Value for the money, lots of features
reviews.reviewText: For the money this may be the best bargain out there with many much needed features, I like the 2.5G ethernet for future use and more than 2 memory slots is a plus, And it has a m2 slot as well. This was an upgrade for my gaming rig and was easy to install without any issues. I did this on a budget as I didn't want to spend a lot of money. I couldn't be more pleased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Unsatisfactory Product Quality
reviews.reviewText: When I received the motherboard, I did a visual inspection and I was proud to say there was nothing wrong. However, once I took off the CPU socket cover there was 2 bent pins. I didn’t want to return the board seeing that I wanted the computer built quickly, so I used my tiny needle nose pliers to straighten the pins. I have had no problems with the CPU or the socket pins damaging my CPU. When I went to install the M.2, I could not unscrew it. I’m not sure if it is a machine or hand tightened when assembled, but I have used every method I know and could find but to no avail. I have used the 2nd M.2 slot instead. I think for the price I was expecting something with a bit more quality than what I got. I haven’t had any performance issues with it, but it is frustrating to have to straighten pins and have a M.2 slot screw stuck in the screw mount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Affordable DDR5 LGA 1700 Motherboard with Great Features
reviews.reviewText: Pros:Budget-friendly and packed with impressive featuresIncludes a good Wi-Fi antenna that isn't mentioned in the product descriptionMetal boxing inside the motherboard helps with cooling and ensures consistent performanceComes with 4 DDR5 slots and plenty of SATA connectors, providing flexibility to expand the systemEasy to install and highly customizable BIOS with numerous options to adjust performanceCons:Only 1 RGB header, which could be a deal-breaker for RGB enthusiastsRGB Fusion software isn't very user-friendly and tends to change colors incorrectlyLacks a front USB Type-C header, which could be an issue for users who need this featureOverall, the GIGABYTE B760M DS3H AX is an excellent choice for anyone on a mid-range budget looking for an affordable DDR5 LGA 1700 motherboard with great features. While there are some limitations to this motherboard, its price and performance make it a worthwhile investment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not fancy but has the performance
reviews.reviewText: This motherboard isn't fancy with extras, but supports 13th gen intel processors, along with 14th gen with the proper firmware update.Even though I was shopping cheap as possible, this board has not disappointed me.Keeping cheap with DDR4 ram and future upgradeability, along with the ability to update the firmware without a processor, this motherboard is an impressive budget pick.

Received a unit that was clearly used - had been fully installed at least once and was missing the instruction manual. (Inspected - really?) It didn't look 'bad' so proceed to install .... and then determined that this item was the 'bad' component in the system. If you are new to building a PC or working to meet a deadline, then this open-box probably isn't a good choice. The return process went smoothly and we don't regret trying it.
